## Livestock Slaughter Procedure
- 3 distinct stages
	- pre-slaughter handling
	- stunning
	- slaughtering
- In the US the humane treatment of animals during each of these stages is required by the Humane Slaughter Act
- RA 8485 (Animal Welface Act of 1998) particularly Section 6(7) paragraph 2 &3
	- provides that the killing of animals shall be done through humane procedures at all times
	- means the use of the most scientific methods available as may be determined and approved by DA Committee on Animal Welfare
- DA AO No. 21B series of 1999 entitled: Code of Conduct (missing)
